From: PS4 Linux Baikal Port <noreply@ps4-linux>
Subject: [PATCH] amdgpu: v33 - skip ATOM PLL/timing in mode_set for Liverpool

Option C (skip DPMS_ON only) didn't restore backlight. mode_set ALSO
calls amdgpu_atombios_crtc_set_pll + set_dtd_timing which use broken
ATOM BIOS on PS4 6.x (ACPI mutex acquire fails).  Those ATOM calls
program the GPU's PLL/timing with garbage, destroying the BIOS-default
DP TX state and breaking the bridge's HDMI signal.

Skip ATOM PLL/timing programming in mode_set for Liverpool.  Only
do_set_base (fb scanout update) and cursor_reset run -- those write
GPU registers directly without ATOM.  GPU PLL stays in BIOS-default
state which the bridge can lock to.

Combined with 0016 (skip DPMS_ON), no ATOM BIOS calls happen during
the modeset chain on Liverpool. fbcon writes still hit VRAM which
BIOS-default DP TX is scanning out.

---
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/dce_v8_0.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/dce_v8_0.c
@@ -2553,6 +2553,8 @@
 {
 	struct amdgpu_crtc *amdgpu_crtc = to_amdgpu_crtc(crtc);
 
+	struct amdgpu_device *adev = drm_to_adev(crtc->dev);
+
 	if (!amdgpu_crtc->adjusted_clock) {
 		/* v28: PS4 ATOM BIOS sometimes returns 0 from
 		 * AdjustDisplayPll (we see "ACPI Error: AE_BAD_PARAMETER"
@@ -2568,6 +2570,16 @@
 		amdgpu_crtc->adjusted_clock = adjusted_mode->clock;
 	}
 
+	/* v33: skip ATOM-BIOS PLL/timing on Liverpool/Gladius - ATOM is broken
+	 * on PS4 6.x (ACPI mutex acquire fails), would corrupt GPU state. */
+	if (adev->asic_type == CHIP_LIVERPOOL || adev->asic_type == CHIP_GLADIUS) {
+		pr_info("dce_v8_0_crtc_mode_set: Liverpool - skipping ATOM PLL/timing, only set_base\n");
+		dce_v8_0_crtc_do_set_base(crtc, old_fb, x, y, 0);
+		dce_v8_0_cursor_reset(crtc);
+		amdgpu_crtc->hw_mode = *adjusted_mode;
+		return 0;
+	}
+
 	amdgpu_atombios_crtc_set_pll(crtc, adjusted_mode);
 	amdgpu_atombios_crtc_set_dtd_timing(crtc, adjusted_mode);
 	dce_v8_0_crtc_do_set_base(crtc, old_fb, x, y, 0);
